  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. The model is intended to predict absolute hemolysis index levels for a Class III VAD device operating at Model Risk Level 5, supporting a regulatory submission claim that predicted hemolysis index does not exceed 0.8 g/100 L under nominal operating conditions (3500–6000 RPM, 4–8 L/min flow). Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across rheological and geometric input parameters. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors are addressed; 7 are fully assessed and 6 are flagged as epistemic gaps consistent with MRL 5 requirements. The intended patient population is adults with end-stage heart failure requiring bridge-to-transplant support. This package conforms to the Minimal profile; the structured Context of Use object is captured in the associated requirement and claim nodes rather than as a standalone hasContextOfUse link.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-vad-cfd-hemolysis-absolute-prediction",
